                  <div class="body">
                    <p>Hi Linda,</p>
<p>Thanks for getting in touch.</p>
<p>We have a 3-step process to see if we can offer coverage for pre-existing medical conditions. We ask that all customers take the time to read through our PDS to confirm our coverage is right for them.</p>
<p><a href="http://ins-admin.tidau.prod.wng.local/Document/OpenRegulatoryWording?RegulatoryWordingTypeId=1" title="PDS">Please click here</a> to view the PDS for full details. You will find the 3-step pre-existing medical process on pages 29-33.</p>
<p>As you will see, under our Step 2 – “Pre-existing medical conditions which are not covered”, we do not cover your pre-existing medical condition if:</p>
<ul>
	<li>You have been diagnosed with any form of cardiovascular disease or received treatment for a related condition.</li>
	<li>Any condition which arises from signs or symptoms that you are currently aware of, but:<br>
a) you have not yet sought a medical opinion regarding the cause; or<br>
b) you are currently under investigation to define a diagnosis; or<br>
c) you are awaiting specialist opinion;</li>
</ul>
<p>If your pre-existing medical conditions are not covered under our policy, you are still welcome to purchase a standard policy with us, just keeping in mind your pre-existing medical conditions will not be covered under this policy.</p>
<p>To get a quote, please visit our website; <a href="http://www.travelinsurancedirect.com.au/" title="website">www.tid.com.au</a>. If you continue through the quote to buy now, the system will take you through our 3-step process to cover pre-existing medical conditions.</p>
<p>You may like to try SureSave: <a href="https://www.suresave.com.au/" title="website">www.suresave.com.au</a> who may be able to assist with covering your pre-existing medical condition.</p>
<p>I hope this has helped. Please let me know if I can be of further assistance to you.</p>
